Description: Lip sherd of Attic, probably black-figured, pottery Siana cup; interior: reserved band at rim, glazed black below; exterior: narrow band at rim above myrtle frieze; inscription on interior.
Bibliographic references: Brijder 1983a / Siana Cups I and Komast Cups (p. 262, no. 281) (Double-Palmette Painter)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.0379) (Phase 1)
